   <h5> <a class="de">&nbsp;</a><span class="cu">Finding My Mom </span>


<span class="crd ntb">(<a href="/comments/1208579/50156779#c2?mode=alone;showrate=1#c2">25+ / 0-</a>)</span>
  </h5>

  
  


<div class="crs"><dl>
  <dt>Recommended by:</dt><dd>
  <a href="/user/uid:332959">Icicle68</a>, <a href="/user/uid:105891">JML9999</a>, <a href="/user/uid:209053">Anthony Page aka SecondComing</a>, <a href="/user/uid:114668">OleHippieChick</a>, <a href="/user/uid:26703">oceanview</a>, <a href="/user/uid:73842">4Freedom</a>, <a href="/user/uid:25604">wishingwell</a>, <a href="/user/uid:13682">eeff</a>, <a href="/user/uid:45368">historys mysteries</a>, <a href="/user/uid:60831">Joes Steven</a>, <a href="/user/uid:226416">sow hat</a>, <a href="/user/uid:198313">tardis10</a>, <a href="/user/uid:63615">RainyDay</a>, <a href="/user/uid:111628">JeffW</a>, <a href="/user/uid:246193">Mr Robert</a>, <a href="/user/uid:54757">PSzymeczek</a>, <a href="/user/uid:199521">wintergreen8694</a>, <a href="/user/uid:146420">maryabein</a>, <a href="/user/uid:112606">angry hopeful liberal</a>, <a href="/user/uid:35666">Steveningen</a>, <a href="/user/uid:165002">renzo capetti</a>, <a href="/user/uid:539192">Shippo1776</a>, <a href="/user/uid:192112">mrsgoo</a>, <a href="/user/uid:106540">eyesoars</a>, <a href="/user/uid:383283">pragmaticidealist</a>
    </dd>
  
</dl></div>

  

  <div class="ct">
  
<p>Fourteen years ago this week, I picked some flowers to decorate my mother's grave and I headed out to All Saints Cemetery.<br />
I guess I had only been there in the limo, because as I felt my way along Rand Road and hit Central, it wasn't there.<br />
To my left at the red light was a Des Plaines police car, so I looked to the officer and asked, "Can you tell me which way I'd go to All Saints Cemetery?"<br />
"What is your mother's name?" he asked.<br />
I told him and he said, "Follow me."<br />
(My mother's name? What was that about?)<br />
The light turned green, then from the center lane he took a wide right in front of me onto Central eastbound, and I turned in right behind him. Within a mile I saw the cemetery fence coming up on the right, so I realized that I had wanted River Road, not Rand Road. (Sorry, Mom.)<br />
I figured he would wave for me to turn, but he drove right in. And I followed, through the labyrinth of circular byways that delineate such a huge cemetery. Then he stopped.<br />
He got out of his squad car and walked back to me and said, "She's right in here."<br />
(On the way he had radioed All Saints and gotten the exact location.)<br />
I told him, "Really, I'm not believing you could do this."<br />
He grinned a little, "You weren't the first one who asked. Happy Mothers Day."</p>
<p>It was.</p>

  </div>
